<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-14443] Mirror Maker Connectors leak admin clients used for topic creation</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-14443</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;the MirrorMaker connectors are each responsible for creating internal topics.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For example, the Checkpoint connector creates a forwarding admin and passes it to a method to create the topic, but never closes the ForwardingAdmin or delegate objects: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/blob/13c9c78a1f4ad92023e8354069c6817b44c89ce6/connect/mirror/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/mirror/MirrorCheckpointConnector.java#L161-L164&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/kafka/blob/13c9c78a1f4ad92023e8354069c6817b44c89ce6/connect/mirror/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/mirror/MirrorCheckpointConnector.java#L161-L164&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Instead, this object should be intentionally closed when it is no longer needed, to prevent consuming resources in a running MM2 application.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
